1
00:00:40,874 --> 00:00:43,286
( Blender whirrs)

2
00:01:32,258 --> 00:01:34,033
( buzzing )

3
00:02:33,153 --> 00:02:35,656
( country music playing )

4
00:02:45,198 --> 00:02:47,644
(woman singing)

5
00:03:01,781 --> 00:03:04,887
(dialing )

6
00:03:11,758 --> 00:03:13,704
It's me, hon.

7
00:03:13,726 --> 00:03:16,297
Listen, I'm in a hell
of a bind here.

8
00:03:16,329 --> 00:03:18,707
I got more problems
than I could deal with on my own.

9
00:03:18,731 --> 00:03:20,870
I need you to come on over.

10
00:03:20,900 --> 00:03:24,473
For Pete's sake, it's nothing
I'd care to discuss over the phone.

11
00:03:24,504 --> 00:03:26,142
Would you just
get yourself over here?

12
00:03:43,122 --> 00:03:45,124
Radio DJ:
It's a fine day today, folks.

13
00:03:45,158 --> 00:03:46,660
It's 1931 --

14
00:03:46,693 --> 00:03:48,969
145 years to the day

15
00:03:48,995 --> 00:03:52,465
since our great state of Texas
declared its independence.

16
00:03:52,498 --> 00:03:55,240
And, boy, I got some Texas tunes
to play for you today.

17
00:03:55,268 --> 00:03:57,544
This is 97.9 Country,

18
00:03:57,570 --> 00:03:59,846
coming at you
like a rattlesnake.

19
00:03:59,872 --> 00:04:01,647
Lorna.

20
00:04:01,674 --> 00:04:03,676
I came as soon
as I hung up the phone.

21
00:04:03,710 --> 00:04:05,451
Oh.

22
00:04:06,479 --> 00:04:08,220
For heaven's sake,

23
00:04:08,248 --> 00:04:10,228
whatever's happened
to Dale?

24
00:04:10,250 --> 00:04:12,287
( Sighs )
Dale's fine.

25
00:04:12,318 --> 00:04:15,925
I just knocked him over the head
with Mama's cast-iron skillet-

26
00:04:15,955 --> 00:04:18,629
nothing a bag of ice
can't take care of.

27
00:04:18,658 --> 00:04:20,604
Jesus, Lorna.

28
00:04:20,627 --> 00:04:22,629
What did you go
and do that for?

29
00:04:22,662 --> 00:04:24,664
I was just trying
to have a polite conversation

30
00:04:24,697 --> 00:04:26,768
between two married
individuals,

31
00:04:26,799 --> 00:04:28,801
but you know Dale.

32
00:04:28,835 --> 00:04:31,941
You can't have a civil debate with
the man without things turning ugly.

33
00:04:31,971 --> 00:04:34,349
Well, Dale was never one for polite
conversation, that's for damn sure.

34
00:04:34,374 --> 00:04:36,376
Forget about Dale.

35
00:04:36,409 --> 00:04:39,322
I got more pressing matters on my plate
than his bruised head.

36
00:04:39,345 --> 00:04:40,756
What's going on?

37
00:04:40,780 --> 00:04:43,954
( Exhales )
It's a wild story, Tiny--

38
00:04:43,983 --> 00:04:46,657
a real wild story.
You ain't gonna believe it.

39
00:04:46,686 --> 00:04:50,065
No, you know me, Lorna.
I believe in stories-

40
00:04:50,089 --> 00:04:52,296
probably why I get myself
into so much trouble.

41
00:04:53,760 --> 00:04:55,535
You hear about this?

42
00:04:55,561 --> 00:04:57,905
- The bank robbery down in Red County?
- Mm-hmm.

43
00:04:57,930 --> 00:05:00,240
It's been all over the news
what happened two days ago.

44
00:05:00,266 --> 00:05:02,143
The police is out still looking
for who done it.

45
00:05:02,168 --> 00:05:05,479
You can't turn on the damn TV
without hearing something about it.

46
00:05:05,505 --> 00:05:08,952
A man wearing a stocking
over his head

47
00:05:08,975 --> 00:05:11,785
just waltzed into
Waldorf Savings & Loan,

48
00:05:11,811 --> 00:05:13,813
tossed a bag on the counter,

49
00:05:13,846 --> 00:05:16,827
pointed a revolver
at the cashier and said,

50
00:05:16,849 --> 00:05:20,592
"Good morning there.
It's your time to shine.

51
00:05:20,620 --> 00:05:23,658
Fill the satchel, hit the floor,
and all will be well."

52
00:05:23,690 --> 00:05:26,102
I heard a heck of a lot of money
has gone missing.

53
00:05:26,125 --> 00:05:28,867
$100,000, all cash.

54
00:05:28,895 --> 00:05:32,707
I didn't think there was that kind of
money in the whole state of Texas,

55
00:05:32,732 --> 00:05:35,076
never mind a bank
in Red County.

56
00:05:36,769 --> 00:05:39,943
- Go ahead, have one of mine.
- Mm-mm, those things will kill you.

57
00:05:39,972 --> 00:05:42,316
Them light cigarettes
you smoke

58
00:05:42,342 --> 00:05:44,219
will kill you just the same,
only slower.

59
00:05:44,243 --> 00:05:46,245
Don't hound me
for trying to buy

60
00:05:46,279 --> 00:05:48,850
a little bit of extra time
on this earth

61
00:05:48,881 --> 00:05:51,259
in case something worthwhile
comes up.

62
00:05:55,788 --> 00:05:58,462
Now tell me about
this great robbery.

63
00:05:58,491 --> 00:06:01,028
I know who went and done it.

64
00:06:01,060 --> 00:06:03,062
You what?

65
00:06:04,230 --> 00:06:06,767
I know who done it, Tiny.

66
00:06:09,001 --> 00:06:11,607
It seems that Dale here

67
00:06:11,637 --> 00:06:13,207
forgot to make me privy

68
00:06:13,239 --> 00:06:16,743
of certain unsavory activities
in the last few days.

69
00:06:16,776 --> 00:06:18,778
( Tiny scoffs )

70
00:06:18,811 --> 00:06:21,587
You mean Dale
gone and robbed that bank?

71
00:06:21,614 --> 00:06:23,423
That's exactly what I mean.

72
00:06:23,449 --> 00:06:25,895
Lorna, just because a man
held up a convenience store

73
00:06:25,918 --> 00:06:29,627
a couple of times
in his more wild and woolly days

74
00:06:29,655 --> 00:06:31,896
don't mean he's a bank robber.

75
00:06:31,924 --> 00:06:34,404
- Five.
- Five?

76
00:06:34,427 --> 00:06:36,429
He robbed five
convenience stores.

77
00:06:36,462 --> 00:06:40,308
It was high time he graduated
to something bigger.

78
00:06:40,333 --> 00:06:41,676
How are you so sure
he done it?

79
00:06:42,835 --> 00:06:44,746
You know why they call it
Red County?

80
00:06:44,771 --> 00:06:46,375
Why?

81
00:06:46,406 --> 00:06:49,148
On account of the iron ore
in the soil,

82
00:06:49,175 --> 00:06:51,712
makes all the dirt red
down there.

83
00:06:53,846 --> 00:06:56,622
Lorna, now he could have
picked up that dirt from anywhere.

84
00:06:56,649 --> 00:07:00,620
Tiny, the soles of them boots are redder
than an Indian'-s face in the sun.

85
00:07:00,653 --> 00:07:04,362
That is Red County soil,
that's for damn sure.

86
00:07:04,390 --> 00:07:07,462
And Dale's got no business
in Red County,

87
00:07:07,493 --> 00:07:09,404
not to mention

88
00:07:09,429 --> 00:07:12,171
that I only got me
one good pair of hose,

89
00:07:12,198 --> 00:07:14,200
and they're nowhere
to be found.

90
00:07:14,233 --> 00:07:18,079
( Chuckles )
He went and took his wife's own hose.

91
00:07:18,104 --> 00:07:19,708
Can you believe the nerves
of that man?

92
00:07:19,739 --> 00:07:23,152
He probably expects
I was never gonna find out.

93
00:07:23,176 --> 00:07:26,555
God, if dumb was dirt,

94
00:07:26,579 --> 00:07:28,616
Dale would cover
about an acre.

95
00:07:30,416 --> 00:07:34,728
So I called me Mr. Gale
down at Gale & Sons-

96
00:07:34,754 --> 00:07:38,292
you know, where he works selling
them modular kitchen cabinets.

97
00:07:39,659 --> 00:07:42,538
You know what
Mr. Gale tells me?

98
00:07:42,562 --> 00:07:45,304
I hope you enjoy
Gardendale, Lorna.

99
00:07:45,331 --> 00:07:47,038
Gardendale?

100
00:07:47,066 --> 00:07:49,706
That's near Lamar County.

101
00:07:49,735 --> 00:07:51,874
Seems like Dale here

102
00:07:51,904 --> 00:07:54,441
filed for a transfer
two days ago.

103
00:07:54,474 --> 00:07:55,646
He what?

104
00:07:55,675 --> 00:07:57,416
Mm-hmm.
Ain't that a hoot?

105
00:07:57,443 --> 00:08:01,084
Figured he'd skip town without
so much as raising an eyebrow.

106
00:08:01,113 --> 00:08:04,651
It don't take much
to flee to Mexico from there.

107
00:08:04,684 --> 00:08:07,255
- Son of a bitch.
- Yeah, my sentiments exactly.

108
00:08:13,459 --> 00:08:17,202
$100.000. Tiny--

109
00:08:17,230 --> 00:08:19,733
that is a hell of a lot
of money.

110
00:08:19,765 --> 00:08:23,076
And he wasn't gonna share
a penny of it.

111
00:08:25,938 --> 00:08:27,212
What are you gonna do
about it?

112
00:08:27,240 --> 00:08:30,653
I figured I'd rather split that money
with a good friend

113
00:08:30,676 --> 00:08:33,623
than let that thieving dog of a husband
get away with it.

114
00:08:33,646 --> 00:08:36,490
I ain't gonna sit here
and disagree with that.

115
00:08:40,520 --> 00:08:43,296
- But one thing.
- What's that?

116
00:08:44,590 --> 00:08:46,035
Where's the money?

117
00:08:47,393 --> 00:08:50,374
That's what I'm fixing
to find out.

118
00:08:56,802 --> 00:08:59,282
( Exclaims )
What the hell?

119
00:08:59,305 --> 00:09:00,716
Welcome back, hon.

120
00:09:00,740 --> 00:09:02,310
( Country music playing )

121
00:09:02,341 --> 00:09:03,513
Oh, what's going on?

122
00:09:03,543 --> 00:09:05,921
Sorry, Dale, but we got
pressing matters to discuss

123
00:09:05,945 --> 00:09:07,856
and I need the benefit
of restraints.

124
00:09:07,880 --> 00:09:09,484
You know how you can get.

125
00:09:09,515 --> 00:09:12,121
(grunts )You get me out of here
right this minute,

126
00:09:12,151 --> 00:09:15,621
or I swear I will kick in every single
one of your teeth one at a time, Lorna.

127
00:09:15,655 --> 00:09:17,931
No need to get
confrontational now, Dale.

128
00:09:17,957 --> 00:09:19,459
( Exhales )

129
00:09:19,492 --> 00:09:22,530
I need you to talk
and I need you to be composed.

130
00:09:22,562 --> 00:09:24,166
I will give you composed.

131
00:09:24,196 --> 00:09:25,675
What did I tell you?

132
00:09:25,698 --> 00:09:28,269
- Not gonna give it up without a fight.
- Mm-mm.

133
00:09:28,301 --> 00:09:30,542
What the hell is she
doing here?

134
00:09:30,570 --> 00:09:32,572
I needed a friend.

135
00:09:32,605 --> 00:09:35,950
When you find out that the man that you
love is nothing but a rattling snake,

136
00:09:35,975 --> 00:09:37,716
sometimes a friend
is all you got.

137
00:09:37,743 --> 00:09:39,154
Amen, Lorna.

138
00:09:39,178 --> 00:09:40,816
What are the two of you
on about?

139
00:09:40,846 --> 00:09:43,258
We're talking about the great robbery
in Red County.

140
00:09:47,787 --> 00:09:49,858
What, you didn't think
I was gonna find out?

141
00:09:49,889 --> 00:09:51,527
I--

142
00:09:51,557 --> 00:09:53,503
- Ask him where's the money.
- Where's the money, Dale?

143
00:09:53,526 --> 00:09:56,029
Wh-- what money?

144
00:09:56,062 --> 00:09:58,133
The $100,000 in cash

145
00:09:58,164 --> 00:10:00,644
you confiscated
from the Waldorf Savings & Loan.

146
00:10:00,666 --> 00:10:04,079
I don't know nothing about
no Waldorf Savings & Loan.

147
00:10:04,103 --> 00:10:06,515
You didn't know about the string
of convenience store robberies neither

148
00:10:06,539 --> 00:10:07,847
- three years ago.
- That's right.

149
00:10:07,873 --> 00:10:10,012
Like hell you didn't.
You even went and robbed

150
00:10:10,042 --> 00:10:12,352
Ophenius Dunn's
feed warehouse, Dale.

151
00:10:12,378 --> 00:10:14,756
That was Mama's
second husband.

152
00:10:14,780 --> 00:10:16,623
Did you think he wasn't gonna
identify you?

153
00:10:16,649 --> 00:10:18,686
Well, I did not expect
his identification of me

154
00:10:18,718 --> 00:10:20,459
on account
he wears trifocals.

155
00:10:20,486 --> 00:10:23,194
I did my three years.
I paid my debt to society.

156
00:10:23,222 --> 00:10:25,498
God damn you, Dale.

157
00:10:25,524 --> 00:10:28,630
You promised me.
You looked me straight in the eye

158
00:10:28,661 --> 00:10:31,198
and you gave me your word
you were done with your criminal ways.

159
00:10:31,230 --> 00:10:32,641
I am.
That's a fact.

160
00:10:32,665 --> 00:10:35,168
I ain't in the business
of getting in trouble no more.

161
00:10:35,201 --> 00:10:38,739
I'm straight as a duck
with two good wings.

162
00:10:38,771 --> 00:10:40,216
Is that right?

163
00:10:40,239 --> 00:10:42,241
Cross my heart
and hope to die.

164
00:10:42,274 --> 00:10:45,380
Nothing but the joy
of modular cabinetry

165
00:10:45,411 --> 00:10:47,948
to keep me
righteously occupied.

166
00:10:50,249 --> 00:10:53,662
Well, then you'll gladly tell me

167
00:10:53,686 --> 00:10:57,361
what that is
on the soles of your boots.

168
00:10:57,390 --> 00:10:58,562
What?

169
00:10:59,825 --> 00:11:02,965
Do you know why they call it
Red County, Dale?

170
00:11:05,064 --> 00:11:06,873
No.

171
00:11:06,899 --> 00:11:10,244
On account of the iron ore
in the soil.

172
00:11:10,269 --> 00:11:13,045
Iron ore in the soil?

173
00:11:13,072 --> 00:11:15,279
Ho-ho! Whoo!

174
00:11:15,307 --> 00:11:19,084
You sure got a hell of
a fervent imagination, Lorna.

175
00:11:21,047 --> 00:11:22,583
Did I imagine this?

176
00:11:25,217 --> 00:11:27,629
Where in hell did you get
a peashooter like that?

177
00:11:27,653 --> 00:11:30,224
I got it where I get all the things
you're trying to hide from me--

178
00:11:30,256 --> 00:11:32,258
underneath the floorboard
in the bathroom.

179
00:11:33,693 --> 00:11:35,604
I've never seen that before
in my life.

180
00:11:35,628 --> 00:11:36,936
You're lying.

181
00:11:36,962 --> 00:11:39,306
What would you
base that statement on?

182
00:11:39,331 --> 00:11:41,470
On the fact that you never tell
nothing but lies.

183
00:11:41,500 --> 00:11:44,276
You was lying before you learned
how to talk.

184
00:11:44,303 --> 00:11:47,580
Nothing but the pure gospel truth
ever passed these lips.

185
00:11:47,606 --> 00:11:49,813
So you're telling me

186
00:11:49,842 --> 00:11:52,152
that you don't know nothing
about no robbery.

187
00:11:52,178 --> 00:11:54,454
I know nothing about
the robbery.

188
00:11:54,480 --> 00:11:56,482
And you ain't never seen
this gun before?

189
00:11:56,515 --> 00:11:58,358
Yes, ma'am.

190
00:11:59,685 --> 00:12:03,690
For crying out loud,
where are my nerve tablets?

191
00:12:08,260 --> 00:12:10,536
( Exhales )

192
00:12:16,001 --> 00:12:17,639
What are you looking at?

193
00:12:17,670 --> 00:12:20,583
You got your mama's legs.

194
00:12:20,606 --> 00:12:22,779
Mama's got
real pretty legs.

195
00:12:22,808 --> 00:12:25,584
They're long and white
like Milkybars.

196
00:12:25,611 --> 00:12:28,717
Mm, I always did want
to bed your mama.

197
00:12:28,748 --> 00:12:31,024
- God damn you, Dale.
- I'm an honest man.

198
00:12:31,050 --> 00:12:32,654
I swear to God,

199
00:12:32,685 --> 00:12:35,859
if you have got
the slightest shine for your life,

200
00:12:35,888 --> 00:12:38,334
I suggest you tell me
where that money is,

201
00:12:38,357 --> 00:12:41,031
as I will not be responsible
for my ensuing ways.

202
00:12:41,060 --> 00:12:42,334
- Now wait just a minute.
- What?

203
00:12:42,361 --> 00:12:44,637
- You can't shoot him.
- Why the hell not?

204
00:12:49,635 --> 00:12:53,139
We are talking about
a lot of money here, Tiny.

205
00:12:53,172 --> 00:12:54,776
Tiny: Right.

206
00:12:54,807 --> 00:12:56,684
Lorna: And Dale here

207
00:12:56,709 --> 00:13:00,816
is one hell
of a pertinacious individual.

208
00:13:00,846 --> 00:13:02,052
Come on now.

209
00:13:02,081 --> 00:13:04,994
He's gonna need a lot of coaxing
to get that information out of him.

210
00:13:05,017 --> 00:13:07,395
Lorna, I guess he is
your husband.

211
00:13:08,954 --> 00:13:12,367
You go ahead and shoot him.
It ain't none of my business.

212
00:13:12,391 --> 00:13:13,734
-( Cocks gun )
- Oh, wait.

213
00:13:13,759 --> 00:13:16,433
-( Gunshot)
-( Dale screams)

214
00:13:17,496 --> 00:13:19,942
No need to turn
belligerent now.

215
00:13:19,965 --> 00:13:21,467
(whimpers)

216
00:13:21,500 --> 00:13:23,411
You ready to talk
like civilized folks?

217
00:13:23,435 --> 00:13:25,915
You know me--
nothing but civilized.

218
00:13:25,938 --> 00:13:27,383
Honey, you scared me.

219
00:13:27,406 --> 00:13:30,751
- You stole that money.
- I did not take that money.

220
00:13:30,776 --> 00:13:32,847
- Damn it.
- Argh! I took that money.

221
00:13:32,878 --> 00:13:36,587
Damn it, Dale, why the hell
did you go and do that for?

222
00:13:36,615 --> 00:13:38,151
It's in my blood.

223
00:13:38,184 --> 00:13:40,858
I can't seem to stay away
from institutions

224
00:13:40,886 --> 00:13:44,163
that contain any significant amount
of legal tender.

225
00:13:44,190 --> 00:13:45,760
Oh, Jesus.

226
00:13:45,791 --> 00:13:48,670
But I was gonna tell you all about it
when the time was right.

227
00:13:48,694 --> 00:13:50,640
Oh, and when would that be?
When you're good and gone?

228
00:13:50,663 --> 00:13:52,802
You never had a lick of confidence
in me, Lorna.

229
00:13:52,832 --> 00:13:55,142
That's what I'm talking about.
That's one of my beefs.

230
00:13:55,167 --> 00:13:59,172
I just figured a woman didn't need
to trouble her pretty little head

231
00:13:59,205 --> 00:14:01,276
with financial matters.

232
00:14:01,307 --> 00:14:04,880
And I-- I-- I was working on it.

233
00:14:04,910 --> 00:14:07,652
That's a man's job anyway.

234
00:14:07,680 --> 00:14:10,752
You just let good old Dale
take care of the details,

235
00:14:10,783 --> 00:14:13,229
and it will all work out
just dandy.

236
00:14:13,252 --> 00:14:16,529
Nothing ever works out just dandy
when you're concerned, Dale.

237
00:14:16,555 --> 00:14:19,661
I admit the whims of fate
have plotted against me in the past,

238
00:14:19,692 --> 00:14:22,468
but I sense the winds
of good fortune

239
00:14:22,494 --> 00:14:25,031
are finally blowing
my merry way.

240
00:14:25,064 --> 00:14:27,066
To hell with your winds, Dale.

241
00:14:27,099 --> 00:14:29,079
All I care about is that money.

242
00:14:29,101 --> 00:14:30,478
Now where is it?

243
00:14:30,502 --> 00:14:33,574
A safe place.
Just get these restraints off me

244
00:14:33,606 --> 00:14:35,415
and I'll take you right to it.
I'll tell you everything.

245
00:14:35,441 --> 00:14:37,443
Oh, not a chance in hell.

246
00:14:37,476 --> 00:14:39,717
Well, we're gonna have
to cooperate on this one, Lorna.

247
00:14:39,745 --> 00:14:41,190
It is a tit for tat here.

248
00:14:41,213 --> 00:14:42,783
He's not gonna talk.

249
00:14:42,815 --> 00:14:44,658
No, I don't think he is.

250
00:14:44,683 --> 00:14:46,492
You're gonna have to
shoot him again.

251
00:14:46,518 --> 00:14:48,657
- I think I just might.
- Now hang on there.

252
00:14:48,687 --> 00:14:52,863
If there is one thing I learned
from being married to you for 17 years,

253
00:14:52,892 --> 00:14:55,634
it's that I know you
like the back of my hand.

254
00:14:57,963 --> 00:14:58,964
Wait a minute.

255
00:14:58,998 --> 00:15:01,444
I figured out
you stole that money.

256
00:15:01,467 --> 00:15:02,468
Oh.

257
00:15:02,501 --> 00:15:05,482
And I can figure out where you hid it,
with or without your help.

258
00:15:08,540 --> 00:15:10,611
What? What? What?

259
00:15:10,643 --> 00:15:13,249
Oh, I don't believe it.

260
00:15:13,279 --> 00:15:14,280
What?

261
00:15:14,313 --> 00:15:15,883
It's right here
in this house, ain't it?

262
00:15:15,915 --> 00:15:17,155
- No, it's not.
- The money's here?

263
00:15:17,182 --> 00:15:18,183
No, it's not.

264
00:15:18,217 --> 00:15:20,857
Oh, my God.
( laughs)

265
00:15:20,886 --> 00:15:22,888
Leave it to Dale.

266
00:15:22,922 --> 00:15:25,926
Who would be foolish enough
to leave the stolen money

267
00:15:25,958 --> 00:15:27,733
right here
in his own domicile?

268
00:15:27,760 --> 00:15:29,831
It's not here, I swear to God
and all the angels.

269
00:15:29,862 --> 00:15:31,535
What did I tell you, Tiny?

270
00:15:31,563 --> 00:15:34,100
I married a lying, cheating-

271
00:15:34,133 --> 00:15:36,340
(gunshot)

272
00:15:36,368 --> 00:15:38,814
-( distant dog barking )
-( blood pattering )

273
00:15:42,408 --> 00:15:44,410
Shit.

274
00:15:49,114 --> 00:15:51,116
Lorna.

275
00:15:51,150 --> 00:15:53,152
Yeah?

276
00:15:57,189 --> 00:15:59,465
Did you just go and kill Dale?

277
00:16:01,727 --> 00:16:04,173
I do believe I just did.

278
00:16:07,599 --> 00:16:09,943
Oh, my God, Lorna.

279
00:16:09,969 --> 00:16:11,676
Oh, my God.

280
00:16:11,704 --> 00:16:13,877
L-- I-- I-- I didn't know
what happened.

281
00:16:13,906 --> 00:16:15,715
I was just
holding the gun like--

282
00:16:15,741 --> 00:16:18,915
Well, Jesus, just put it down,
will you?

283
00:16:18,944 --> 00:16:21,618
L-- I didn't mean to do it.

284
00:16:21,647 --> 00:16:23,957
I just get so worked up
about all this business.

285
00:16:23,983 --> 00:16:26,691
- The gun just went off.
- Holy Jesus.

286
00:16:28,420 --> 00:16:30,058
Dale's dead.

287
00:16:31,490 --> 00:16:34,061
Well, I can see that
for myself, Tiny.

288
00:16:34,093 --> 00:16:37,097
Oh, my God, Lorna,
you went and killed Dale.

289
00:16:37,129 --> 00:16:39,234
(whimpering)

290
00:16:43,002 --> 00:16:44,504
( radio DJ speaking )

291
00:16:44,536 --> 00:16:46,209
Okay.

292
00:16:46,238 --> 00:16:48,616
DJ: And now for something
really special.

293
00:17:02,187 --> 00:17:05,031
All right now.

294
00:17:05,057 --> 00:17:07,594
- Okay.
- Wh--? Wh--?

295
00:17:07,626 --> 00:17:10,334
What's done is done.
Everything is gonna be

296
00:17:10,362 --> 00:17:12,364
just fine.

297
00:17:12,398 --> 00:17:14,571
We gotta keep our
heads together.

298
00:17:16,468 --> 00:17:17,970
That's nice.

299
00:17:18,003 --> 00:17:19,505
That's all better.

300
00:17:20,806 --> 00:17:23,980
Now this is no time
to be losing our wit.

301
00:17:24,009 --> 00:17:26,580
We got ourselves
a dead body here.

302
00:17:27,980 --> 00:17:30,153
What are we supposed to do?

303
00:17:30,182 --> 00:17:32,025
Well, I don't know, Tiny.

304
00:17:32,051 --> 00:17:34,429
I've never dealt
with a dead body before.

305
00:17:34,453 --> 00:17:36,490
I thought you might,
because you're the one that killed him.

306
00:17:36,522 --> 00:17:38,593
( Hisses )
Well, it was an accident.

307
00:17:40,926 --> 00:17:44,066
We've got a hell of a situation
on our hands here, Lorna.

308
00:17:47,666 --> 00:17:49,236
Oh, Jesus.

309
00:17:49,268 --> 00:17:51,305
L-- I--

310
00:17:51,336 --> 00:17:53,543
I can't stand for him to stare
at me like that.

311
00:17:53,572 --> 00:17:55,882
- Would you do something?
- Me?

312
00:17:55,908 --> 00:17:57,819
I think I got something.

313
00:17:59,311 --> 00:18:00,881
Uh...

314
00:18:08,554 --> 00:18:10,397
This ought to do it.

315
00:18:12,024 --> 00:18:13,025
Here.

316
00:18:14,193 --> 00:18:15,797
No. What do you want me
to do with that?

317
00:18:15,828 --> 00:18:17,398
Put it over his head,
would you?

318
00:18:18,730 --> 00:18:21,404
You do it.
You-- you just wait a minute.

319
00:18:21,433 --> 00:18:23,504
I can't stand him
staring at me like that.

320
00:18:23,535 --> 00:18:25,742
- Well, then why don't you do it?
- Because I shot him.

321
00:18:25,771 --> 00:18:27,375
You gotta put the bag
over his head.

322
00:18:27,406 --> 00:18:29,044
My God, can I have
a little bit of help here?

323
00:18:29,074 --> 00:18:30,815
Do I have to do
everything myself?!

324
00:18:46,125 --> 00:18:48,935
Ugh.

325
00:18:50,062 --> 00:18:53,066
Well, that's a bit better.

326
00:18:55,767 --> 00:18:57,269
Better?

327
00:18:59,104 --> 00:19:02,551
Lorna, that bag
does not hide the fact

328
00:19:02,574 --> 00:19:04,485
that there's a dead man
underneath it!

329
00:19:04,510 --> 00:19:06,217
Oh.

330
00:19:06,245 --> 00:19:08,748
I never graduated high school
or nothing.

331
00:19:08,780 --> 00:19:11,056
Just give me a moment
to think.

332
00:19:28,167 --> 00:19:30,704
(dialing phone)

333
00:19:32,070 --> 00:19:33,811
What the hell do you think
you're doing?

334
00:19:33,839 --> 00:19:35,409
I'm gonna call the police.

335
00:19:35,440 --> 00:19:37,579
Are you out of your mind?

336
00:19:37,609 --> 00:19:40,488
It was an accident.
The gun just went off.

337
00:19:40,512 --> 00:19:42,788
Tiny, we are in Texas.

338
00:19:42,814 --> 00:19:44,794
There are no accidents.

339
00:19:44,816 --> 00:19:47,228
There's alive and there's dead.

340
00:19:53,225 --> 00:19:55,296
You didn't mean to kill him.

341
00:19:55,327 --> 00:19:56,931
Who's gonna believe that?

342
00:19:56,962 --> 00:20:00,842
We got a dead man tied to a chair
and $100,000 missing.

343
00:20:00,866 --> 00:20:03,642
We're gonna look real good in court
explaining that story.

344
00:20:03,669 --> 00:20:06,206
We? What do you mean, we?

345
00:20:06,238 --> 00:20:07,876
I didn't kill nobody.

346
00:20:07,906 --> 00:20:09,442
You think they'd care
to split that hair?

347
00:20:09,474 --> 00:20:12,387
You was here when it happened,
and that's all they need to know

348
00:20:12,411 --> 00:20:14,516
to lock us both away
for a real long time.

349
00:20:22,688 --> 00:20:24,827
Well, you think it was
self-defense of some kind?

350
00:20:26,558 --> 00:20:29,505
Well, I ain't no officer of the law
or nothing,

351
00:20:29,528 --> 00:20:32,805
but we got a man
tied to a chair.

352
00:20:32,831 --> 00:20:35,744
He don't seem to pose
no immediate threat, now do he?

353
00:20:36,735 --> 00:20:38,408
(Tiny sighs)

354
00:20:38,437 --> 00:20:40,644
Jesus Christ, Tiny.

355
00:20:40,672 --> 00:20:44,848
I don't know nothing
about no self-defense.

356
00:20:44,876 --> 00:20:47,755
It could be first-degree murder,
for all we know.

357
00:20:47,779 --> 00:20:50,623
( Sighs ) Look, that money
is here somewhere.

358
00:20:50,649 --> 00:20:52,959
We got a whole new life
to look forward to.

359
00:20:54,086 --> 00:20:57,761
I am not gonna spend it in a goddamn
cell, I can promise you that.

360
00:21:10,702 --> 00:21:13,114
You know,

361
00:21:13,138 --> 00:21:16,278
I remember hearing a story
growing up.

362
00:21:16,308 --> 00:21:18,151
What story?

363
00:21:19,344 --> 00:21:22,018
My daddy worked the oil fields
in Houston

364
00:21:22,047 --> 00:21:24,084
before he moved out here.

365
00:21:24,116 --> 00:21:26,357
Well, it was a while back.

366
00:21:26,385 --> 00:21:28,956
He'd just started out
as afield landsman

367
00:21:28,987 --> 00:21:30,989
when one of the wells
he was working on

368
00:21:31,023 --> 00:21:33,060
just went and blew up.

369
00:21:33,091 --> 00:21:35,264
Three men was buried alive.

370
00:21:36,995 --> 00:21:40,101
They tried like hell
to get them out.

371
00:21:40,132 --> 00:21:42,806
Daddy said
he could hear them

372
00:21:42,834 --> 00:21:45,644
crying for help down there
the first day.

373
00:21:47,539 --> 00:21:50,042
But by the second day,

374
00:21:50,075 --> 00:21:53,249
they didn't hear
a darn thing stirring.

375
00:21:53,278 --> 00:21:55,189
They figured
they'd dig them out

376
00:21:55,213 --> 00:21:57,454
and give them
a proper burial, right?

377
00:21:59,651 --> 00:22:01,858
But when they
got to them,

378
00:22:01,887 --> 00:22:05,130
there wasn't much left
to do anything proper with.

379
00:22:05,157 --> 00:22:06,932
What happened?

380
00:22:09,328 --> 00:22:11,137
Bugs.

381
00:22:12,798 --> 00:22:14,471
Bugs?

382
00:22:14,499 --> 00:22:17,412
Them Texas bugs
done got to them.

383
00:22:18,570 --> 00:22:20,072
No kidding.

384
00:22:21,073 --> 00:22:22,677
Oh, yeah.

385
00:22:22,708 --> 00:22:25,621
Them Texas bugs can eat
right through a metal can

386
00:22:25,644 --> 00:22:28,284
if there's something tasty
to get inside at.

387
00:22:28,313 --> 00:22:30,793
They got jaws
like lawn mowers.

388
00:22:30,816 --> 00:22:34,457
They just up and left
nothing behind.

389
00:22:34,486 --> 00:22:36,625
I never knew
bugs could do that.

390
00:22:37,856 --> 00:22:41,201
Such is the wonderment-s
of nature, Tiny.

391
00:22:45,764 --> 00:22:47,038
So you're thinking...

392
00:22:47,065 --> 00:22:49,067
I'm thinking.

393
00:22:49,101 --> 00:22:52,742
What if we was to bury Dale
out there like them oil riggers?

394
00:22:52,771 --> 00:22:54,444
- Go on.
- Chances are,

395
00:22:54,473 --> 00:22:57,215
no one would ever find him
in any recognizable form.

396
00:22:57,242 --> 00:23:00,746
I mean, it's a big stretch
of desert out there.

397
00:23:00,779 --> 00:23:03,453
Full of all types
of carnivorous critters.

398
00:23:03,482 --> 00:23:06,554
Right. Earth to earth,
dust to dust and all that.

399
00:23:06,585 --> 00:23:08,587
- That ain't a hell of a bad idea.
- Mm-hmm.

400
00:23:08,620 --> 00:23:10,622
But it's gonna have to wait.

401
00:23:10,655 --> 00:23:11,827
Why?

402
00:23:11,857 --> 00:23:13,928
Because we gotta find us
that money.

403
00:23:13,959 --> 00:23:16,599
And I figure that we don't got
a lot of time.

404
00:23:25,203 --> 00:23:28,377
♪ Mm-hmm, lingering love ♪

405
00:23:28,407 --> 00:23:31,513
♪ Well, well, won't let me be ♪

406
00:23:31,543 --> 00:23:35,252
♪ Mm-hmm, lingering love... ♪

407
00:23:35,280 --> 00:23:36,850
Watch yourself.

408
00:23:36,882 --> 00:23:38,384
Dale was afraid of rats.

409
00:23:38,417 --> 00:23:40,761
There's rat traps
all over this goddamn place.

