426
00:24:31,503 --> 00:24:33,676
♪ Lingers on and on. ♪

427
00:24:33,705 --> 00:24:36,709
- Radio DJ: Hope you're having a fine...
- Ain't nothing but rat traps in there.

428
00:24:36,741 --> 00:24:37,811
Keep looking.

429
00:24:37,843 --> 00:24:41,689
Radio DJ: And now a great tune
to make your day even better.

430
00:24:41,713 --> 00:24:44,023
How are you so sure
the money is even here?

431
00:24:44,049 --> 00:24:46,620
'Cause I know Dale.
The money's here. I'm sure of it.

432
00:24:48,787 --> 00:24:52,633
$100.000.

433
00:24:54,125 --> 00:24:57,106
I can't even imagine
what that might look like.

434
00:24:58,196 --> 00:25:01,075
Yeah, it's more money than this town
has ever seen, that's for damn sure.

435
00:25:01,099 --> 00:25:04,046
You ever think about
what you'd do with that kind of money?

436
00:25:04,069 --> 00:25:06,242
I'd get the hell out of this place,
for one.

437
00:25:10,108 --> 00:25:11,917
Anyplace you ever thought
about going?

438
00:25:12,944 --> 00:25:15,151
I never really thought
about it.

439
00:25:16,147 --> 00:25:19,390
I guess I figured
I'd never really get out of here.

440
00:25:19,417 --> 00:25:22,921
Getting out of this town
is all I ever think about.

441
00:25:23,922 --> 00:25:25,765
(sighs)

442
00:25:25,790 --> 00:25:28,634
You know, I hear
Odessa can be really nice

443
00:25:28,660 --> 00:25:31,402
if you know
your way around.

444
00:25:31,429 --> 00:25:33,030
Hmm.

445
00:25:33,031 --> 00:25:33,372


446
00:25:45,243 --> 00:25:48,019
-( Distant dog barking )
-( car approaching)

447
00:25:48,046 --> 00:25:50,754
Sounds like we got company.

448
00:25:57,689 --> 00:26:00,568
( gasps )
Holy shit, Tiny. It's the law.

449
00:26:00,592 --> 00:26:03,334
How did they get here
so quick?

450
00:26:03,361 --> 00:26:05,136
Lorna: Oh, who else but Dale
would hold up a bank

451
00:26:05,163 --> 00:26:07,074
and hide out in their own home
with all the evidence.

452
00:26:07,098 --> 00:26:09,203
I told you it was just
a matter of time

453
00:26:09,234 --> 00:26:11,840
before they suspected
I was married to a bona fide fool.

454
00:26:11,870 --> 00:26:13,679
What are we gonna do?

455
00:26:15,540 --> 00:26:17,213
-( Both sigh )
- Shit.

456
00:26:17,242 --> 00:26:20,018
Come on, this way.
Just you push and I pull.

457
00:26:20,045 --> 00:26:21,786
Come on now.

458
00:26:21,813 --> 00:26:22,985
Tiny: Oh, God.

459
00:26:23,014 --> 00:26:25,085
Lorna: Push.

460
00:26:25,116 --> 00:26:27,392
Oh, you got it.
Oh, God.

461
00:26:27,419 --> 00:26:28,762
Lorna: That's good.
Okay.

462
00:26:28,787 --> 00:26:31,324
I didn't know they decomposed
so quickly.

463
00:26:31,356 --> 00:26:33,427
Ugh. All right.

464
00:26:33,458 --> 00:26:35,961
- Clean that up a little bit.
- Okay.

465
00:26:38,196 --> 00:26:39,869
Oh, jeez. Hurry up.

466
00:26:44,069 --> 00:26:46,071
Lorna: How do I look?

467
00:26:47,439 --> 00:26:49,885
- Blood.
- Oh, God.

468
00:26:56,915 --> 00:26:58,417
Shit.

469
00:27:05,790 --> 00:27:07,565
Good morning, Sheriff Cooley.

470
00:27:07,592 --> 00:27:09,503
Good morning, Lorna.

471
00:27:09,527 --> 00:27:10,870
What can I do for you?

472
00:27:10,895 --> 00:27:13,671
Looks like you're having yourselves
a little event.

473
00:27:13,698 --> 00:27:15,700
( Lorna chuckles)
No event, Sheriff.

474
00:27:15,734 --> 00:27:17,543
Just a good friend of mine
stopped by

475
00:27:17,569 --> 00:27:19,105
to pay a little visit.

476
00:27:19,137 --> 00:27:22,118
Oh. Mind if I ask
what's the special occasion?

477
00:27:22,140 --> 00:27:24,450
Two friends don't need
a special occasion

478
00:27:24,476 --> 00:27:27,548
to share a little chat
and some homemade lemonade.

479
00:27:27,579 --> 00:27:30,924
Last I checked,
fraternizing ain't against the law.

480
00:27:32,017 --> 00:27:35,396
Is there something
I could help you with today, Sheriff?

481
00:27:35,420 --> 00:27:37,457
Yeah, is Dale around?

482
00:27:37,489 --> 00:27:39,526
No. Dale's out.

483
00:27:39,557 --> 00:27:41,195
Is that right?

484
00:27:41,226 --> 00:27:43,797
I'm pretty sure that's his
station wagon right over here.

485
00:27:43,828 --> 00:27:45,933
Lorna: Well, he didn't drive
his car today.

486
00:27:45,964 --> 00:27:48,535
As a matter of fact,
Dale decided

487
00:27:48,566 --> 00:27:51,445
to go for a little walk
to clear his mind.

488
00:27:51,469 --> 00:27:53,745
A bit hot for a walk, ain't it?

489
00:27:53,772 --> 00:27:56,048
You know Dale, Sheriff.

490
00:27:56,074 --> 00:27:58,384
He likes to do
as he please.

491
00:27:58,410 --> 00:28:01,152
What do you need to see
my dear husband about?

492
00:28:01,179 --> 00:28:04,786
Did you perchance hear about
that holdup down in Red County?

493
00:28:04,816 --> 00:28:06,489
Mm, the great robbery?

494
00:28:06,518 --> 00:28:08,725
The one.

495
00:28:08,753 --> 00:28:10,255
It's all over the news.

496
00:28:10,288 --> 00:28:12,564
First thing that came to mind
when I heard about it

497
00:28:12,590 --> 00:28:14,592
was paying Dale here
a visit--

498
00:28:14,626 --> 00:28:19,166
you know, with his flagrant
predisposition for thievery.

499
00:28:19,197 --> 00:28:21,677
You're barking up
the wrong tree, Sheriff.

500
00:28:21,700 --> 00:28:24,340
Dale has long abandoned
his criminal ways

501
00:28:24,369 --> 00:28:28,317
for the gratifying world
of modular cabinet sales.

502
00:28:28,339 --> 00:28:30,148
Yes, so I've heard.

503
00:28:30,175 --> 00:28:32,382
And how are things
down at Gale & Sons?

504
00:28:32,410 --> 00:28:35,482
Well, business has been
a little slow,

505
00:28:35,513 --> 00:28:37,220
as a matter of fact,

506
00:28:37,248 --> 00:28:40,320
not a lot of demand
for modular cabinetry of late.

507
00:28:40,351 --> 00:28:43,127
About that lemonade-

508
00:28:43,154 --> 00:28:45,191
I sure could use a glass.

509
00:28:45,223 --> 00:28:47,635
Not really a good time, Sheriff.

510
00:28:47,659 --> 00:28:50,162
We're having a bit
of a girls' day.

511
00:28:50,195 --> 00:28:52,801
Don't want to spoil it
by dwelling

512
00:28:52,831 --> 00:28:55,437
on Dale's past delinquent
transgressions.

513
00:28:57,035 --> 00:29:00,209
This won't take long. I'll just
have myself a glass of lemonade,

514
00:29:00,238 --> 00:29:02,240
take a little peek around.

515
00:29:02,273 --> 00:29:05,186
Lorna: Sheriff Cooley,
if there's nothing I learned

516
00:29:05,210 --> 00:29:07,087
from Dale's past
scrapes with the law,

517
00:29:07,112 --> 00:29:10,924
it's that you need yourself
some kind of exigent circumstance

518
00:29:10,949 --> 00:29:13,725
to come into my premises
without a warrant.

519
00:29:13,752 --> 00:29:16,096
And as far as I can tell,
I don't see none.

520
00:29:16,121 --> 00:29:18,931
Well now, I guess
I'm gonna be hard-pressed

521
00:29:18,957 --> 00:29:21,233
to get myself
a search warrant, then.

522
00:29:21,259 --> 00:29:24,331
I hear Judge Wallace likes to go
hunting this time of year.

523
00:29:25,330 --> 00:29:26,536
You know Judge Wallace?

524
00:29:26,564 --> 00:29:29,340
I spent more time with that man
than my own husband

525
00:29:29,367 --> 00:29:32,473
during all them court appearances
a few years back--

526
00:29:32,504 --> 00:29:34,848
a hell of a fine man

527
00:29:34,873 --> 00:29:37,012
with a real love
for the great outdoors.

528
00:29:37,041 --> 00:29:40,716
Mama's third husband goes hunting
with him sometimes in Lamar County.

529
00:29:40,745 --> 00:29:42,747
You really got the heart

530
00:29:42,781 --> 00:29:45,159
to cut short
the judge's hunting trip

531
00:29:45,183 --> 00:29:46,787
just to get that warrant?

532
00:29:46,818 --> 00:29:50,129
Judge Wallace is gonna have to
make do.

533
00:29:50,155 --> 00:29:51,930
Well then,

534
00:29:51,956 --> 00:29:55,403
I guess you'll visit again
once you get your warrant.

535
00:29:56,394 --> 00:30:00,740
I'm just gonna be waiting here till
I get that search warrant in my hands.

536
00:30:12,477 --> 00:30:14,286
Tiny: Oh.

537
00:30:30,995 --> 00:30:32,497
Lorna: What the hell
is he doing?

538
00:30:37,268 --> 00:30:38,770
( Exhales )

539
00:30:47,111 --> 00:30:48,385
( exhales )

540
00:30:48,413 --> 00:30:51,451
Soon you'll be good and done
with all of this, old fella.

541
00:30:53,051 --> 00:30:54,962
Yes, you will.

542
00:31:00,825 --> 00:31:02,133
(starts engine)

543
00:31:13,738 --> 00:31:15,979
We gotta keep
our head on straight.

544
00:31:16,007 --> 00:31:17,714
We don't got much time.

545
00:31:17,742 --> 00:31:21,019
Tiny: How long you figure
before they get him that warrant?

546
00:31:21,045 --> 00:31:23,685
Well, I don't know.
A day, a few hours.

547
00:31:23,715 --> 00:31:26,924
What I do know is Dale can't be here
when he comes back.

548
00:31:26,951 --> 00:31:29,295
Well, let's just bury him somewhere
and let them bugs get at him.

549
00:31:29,320 --> 00:31:31,926
- Holy Christ, Tiny.
- What?

550
00:31:31,956 --> 00:31:33,993
Well, the circumstances
have changed.

551
00:31:34,025 --> 00:31:37,097
That was a good plan before,
but it ain't a good plan now.

552
00:31:37,128 --> 00:31:40,007
We got a sheriff out there

553
00:31:40,031 --> 00:31:41,738
who's watching us
as we speak.

554
00:31:41,766 --> 00:31:46,078
What are we supposed to do, just
waltz a dead body right under his nose?

555
00:31:46,104 --> 00:31:47,674
You're right.

556
00:31:47,705 --> 00:31:50,845
You're right. The situation
has downright thickened.

557
00:31:54,112 --> 00:31:55,819
Let's just make a run for it.

558
00:31:56,814 --> 00:31:59,294
Let's just get in the car,
drive like hell

559
00:31:59,317 --> 00:32:01,695
before anybody
finds out anything.

560
00:32:01,719 --> 00:32:03,426
Are you out of your
little mind?

561
00:32:03,454 --> 00:32:05,764
How long do you think

562
00:32:05,790 --> 00:32:08,066
before they catch up with us?

563
00:32:08,092 --> 00:32:12,666
It's all fine and dandy if you're up
for one of them high-speed car chases,

564
00:32:12,697 --> 00:32:15,940
but I for one am not about
to try to outrun

565
00:32:15,967 --> 00:32:19,744
an army of police cars
in your run-down Pacer.

566
00:32:19,771 --> 00:32:21,773
The damn thing needs
a whole new transmission.

567
00:32:21,806 --> 00:32:23,547
I've been meaning to take it
to the mechanic and--

568
00:32:23,574 --> 00:32:25,281
Oh, for God's sake, Tiny!

569
00:32:25,310 --> 00:32:28,154
Now is not the time to be talking about
no automobile maintenance.

570
00:32:28,179 --> 00:32:30,420
I was just trying
to be helpful, Lorna.

571
00:32:30,448 --> 00:32:32,155
Well, there's no need
to get hostile.

572
00:32:32,183 --> 00:32:35,027
We just need to find ourselves
a sensible solution here.

573
00:32:35,053 --> 00:32:37,897
Well, what do you suggest?

574
00:32:40,458 --> 00:32:41,960
Hmm.

575
00:32:52,403 --> 00:32:54,815
Say we was able

576
00:32:54,839 --> 00:32:57,285
to make Dale disappear

577
00:32:57,308 --> 00:32:59,982
without so much as ever
leaving the house?

578
00:33:01,279 --> 00:33:03,816
When Cooley come back here
with his warrant,

579
00:33:03,848 --> 00:33:07,489
he walk around
and he don't find nothing-

580
00:33:08,686 --> 00:33:11,360
no Dale, no money-

581
00:33:11,389 --> 00:33:13,460
what is he gonna think?

582
00:33:13,491 --> 00:33:15,528
Go on.

583
00:33:15,560 --> 00:33:17,904
He's gonna think

584
00:33:17,929 --> 00:33:20,307
that Dale is good and gone...

585
00:33:21,632 --> 00:33:25,409
took the money with him,
leaving poor old Lorna behind.

586
00:33:25,436 --> 00:33:27,677
A perfectly sensible assumption,
knowing Dale.

587
00:33:27,705 --> 00:33:31,346
Cooley'd be out there
chasing a man that don't exist.

588
00:33:32,677 --> 00:33:36,022
It's gonna take him
a long while

589
00:33:36,047 --> 00:33:38,823
before he
figures anything out,

590
00:33:38,850 --> 00:33:40,352
if he ever do.

591
00:33:40,385 --> 00:33:42,126
Meanwhile...

592
00:33:42,153 --> 00:33:44,190
Meanwhile, we find that money

593
00:33:44,222 --> 00:33:46,759
and as soon as they
look the other way...

594
00:33:46,791 --> 00:33:51,433
We run like hell and just buy ourselves
a whole brand-new life.

595
00:33:51,462 --> 00:33:53,305
You catch on pretty fast.

596
00:33:53,331 --> 00:33:55,106
I like where you're going
with this.

597
00:33:55,133 --> 00:33:57,204
- But--
- But?

598
00:33:59,103 --> 00:34:02,573
Damn it, Lorna,
how do we make Dale disappear?

599
00:34:02,607 --> 00:34:04,450
(sighs)

600
00:34:06,010 --> 00:34:08,217
That there is the pickle.

601
00:34:21,526 --> 00:34:23,699
I think I just
figured out a way.

602
00:34:25,263 --> 00:34:28,301
- How?
- You ain't gonna like it, Tiny.

603
00:34:28,332 --> 00:34:29,936
Try me.

604
00:34:29,967 --> 00:34:31,810
Oh, you ain't gonna
like it one bit.

605
00:34:31,836 --> 00:34:34,578
Lorna, if you have a way
out of this stickler,

606
00:34:34,605 --> 00:34:36,773
I would appreciate
you letting me in on it.

607
00:34:36,774 --> 00:34:37,115


608
00:34:38,176 --> 00:34:40,656
Well,

609
00:34:40,678 --> 00:34:42,487
you know how I fancy myself

610
00:34:42,513 --> 00:34:45,687
a pretty efficient housewife
when the need arises?

611
00:34:45,716 --> 00:34:48,925
Last Thanksgiving,
Dale's folks was planning

612
00:34:48,953 --> 00:34:51,160
to head on over
to Farwell County

613
00:34:51,189 --> 00:34:54,602
for that $6.99 buffet special
at the Rose of Texas motel.

614
00:34:55,660 --> 00:34:59,802
They get as far as Odessa
when they was hit by a dust storm.

615
00:34:59,831 --> 00:35:02,903
The highway patrol
closed all the roads.

616
00:35:02,934 --> 00:35:06,677
They said the cows was being
picked clean off the fields

617
00:35:06,704 --> 00:35:09,378
and flown up in the air
like little old blackbirds.

618
00:35:09,407 --> 00:35:11,614
It was a hell of a storm.

619
00:35:11,642 --> 00:35:14,054
So at the last minute

620
00:35:14,078 --> 00:35:17,525
they decide they're having
Thanksgiving dinner with us.

621
00:35:17,548 --> 00:35:20,825
Some folks have
no manners to speak of.

622
00:35:20,852 --> 00:35:22,889
Please, that is Dale's kin for you.

623
00:35:22,920 --> 00:35:26,197
And you know
how his mama can get.

624
00:35:26,224 --> 00:35:28,670
That woman-- all she ever do
is criticize me.

625
00:35:28,693 --> 00:35:31,435
So...

626
00:35:32,697 --> 00:35:35,769
I had just a few hours
to scrub this place clean,

627
00:35:35,800 --> 00:35:37,837
get rid of all the clutter.

628
00:35:37,869 --> 00:35:42,011
I mean, it was no fancy Rose of Texas
motel or nothing,

629
00:35:42,039 --> 00:35:44,485
but God damn it,
I had the house clean

630
00:35:44,509 --> 00:35:46,887
and I had a 70-pound turkey
with all the fixings

631
00:35:46,911 --> 00:35:49,858
on that table by 9:00.

632
00:35:49,881 --> 00:35:52,452
Now

633
00:35:52,483 --> 00:35:57,193
a woman has got a number
of tools at her disposal

634
00:35:57,221 --> 00:36:00,134
to get things
squared away in no time.

635
00:36:04,295 --> 00:36:06,741
Take this electric
carving knife, for instance,

636
00:36:06,764 --> 00:36:09,711
with an ergonomic handle
for easy maneuvering

637
00:36:09,734 --> 00:36:12,977
and a 12-inch
stainless-steel blade

638
00:36:13,004 --> 00:36:15,280
to cut through
the toughest of bones.

639
00:36:17,441 --> 00:36:20,183
I can't picture this turkey's bones
being any tougher

640
00:36:20,211 --> 00:36:22,487
than a 70-pound bird.

641
00:36:22,513 --> 00:36:25,926
I mean, the man had no spine,
for God's sake.

642
00:36:29,654 --> 00:36:31,998
You're not suggesting...

643
00:36:33,658 --> 00:36:35,604
That's exactly
what I'm suggesting.

644
00:36:37,495 --> 00:36:39,497
You're thinking of
cutting Dale up?

645
00:36:39,530 --> 00:36:43,979
Well, I never took
no science class or nothing,

646
00:36:44,001 --> 00:36:46,709
but I figure the smaller
the pieces,

647
00:36:46,737 --> 00:36:49,013
the easier it will be
to get rid of them.

648
00:36:52,043 --> 00:36:54,045
With a turkey knife?

649
00:36:54,078 --> 00:36:57,321
Well, Tiny, if we wasn't
in such a tad of a hurry,

650
00:36:57,348 --> 00:37:00,352
I would like to do things
with a bit more finesse.

651
00:37:00,384 --> 00:37:03,263
But we are dealing with
time constraints here.

652
00:37:06,657 --> 00:37:09,365
Look,

653
00:37:09,393 --> 00:37:11,771
we'll get Dale

654
00:37:11,796 --> 00:37:14,675
good and disappeared
in a jiffy,

655
00:37:14,699 --> 00:37:18,909
leaving not a trace of him,

656
00:37:18,936 --> 00:37:20,973
like the man never existed.

657
00:37:26,410 --> 00:37:28,754
Are you aware

658
00:37:28,779 --> 00:37:32,727
that just a squirt
of rust remover

659
00:37:32,750 --> 00:37:35,094
can eat through
just about anything?

660
00:37:36,787 --> 00:37:39,324
Mm-mm. Mm-mm.

661
00:37:39,357 --> 00:37:42,861
Well, can you think of any other way
to get through this mess? I can't.

662
00:37:42,893 --> 00:37:44,770
Well, hell, Lorna,
he's your husband.

663
00:37:44,795 --> 00:37:46,502
If you want to cut him up,
that's fine by me.

664
00:37:46,530 --> 00:37:48,840
But I ain't cutting up no man
into little pieces.

665
00:37:49,834 --> 00:37:51,677
I suppose the good Lord

666
00:37:51,702 --> 00:37:53,807
would want me to take care
of this can of worms myself.

667
00:37:53,838 --> 00:37:56,045
I really think He would.

668
00:37:56,073 --> 00:37:57,416
On the other hand,

669
00:37:57,441 --> 00:37:59,443
I don't think the good Lord
would mind too much

670
00:37:59,477 --> 00:38:03,448
if I asked my best friend to help me out
here, due to the circumstances.

671
00:38:03,481 --> 00:38:05,518
For heaven's sake, Lorna,

672
00:38:05,549 --> 00:38:08,223
I ain't cutting up no man
into little pieces.

673
00:38:13,391 --> 00:38:16,531
The man sure liked
a sharp pair of boots.

674
00:38:18,763 --> 00:38:21,004
He knew
how to wear them too.

675
00:38:28,039 --> 00:38:30,041
( Knife buzzing )

676
00:38:35,479 --> 00:38:37,220
-( stops buzzing )
- Oh, God.

677
00:38:37,248 --> 00:38:39,558
Oh, my God.
Oh, my God, Tiny, I can't do this.

678
00:38:39,583 --> 00:38:42,257
- You what?
- I can't do it. I can't do it, Tiny.

679
00:38:42,286 --> 00:38:44,459
I loved the man.

680
00:38:44,488 --> 00:38:46,161
I know he was a son of a bitch
sometimes,

681
00:38:46,190 --> 00:38:47,897
but I swear to God
I loved him.

682
00:38:47,925 --> 00:38:50,269
Don't go soft on me now, Lorna.

683
00:38:50,294 --> 00:38:54,140
Oh, my God, how could I have gone
and done such a terrible thing?

684
00:38:54,165 --> 00:38:56,145
- He got me roses sometimes.
- Lorna.

685
00:38:56,167 --> 00:38:58,408
He'd bring them.
And he could be so sweet. ( muttering )

686
00:38:58,436 --> 00:39:00,643
Lorna, just pull yourself
together now, honey.

687
00:39:00,671 --> 00:39:03,208
- What have I done?
- Just pull yourself together, Lorna.

688
00:39:03,240 --> 00:39:05,516
- Just pull it together.
-( muttering, sobbing )

689
00:39:05,543 --> 00:39:08,285
Now is not the time to be reminiscing.
We've got a job to do.

690
00:39:08,312 --> 00:39:10,314
Oh, Jesus Christ.
I'm so sorry.

691
00:39:10,348 --> 00:39:12,589
Oh, my God, can
You ever forgive me?

692
00:39:12,616 --> 00:39:14,027
( Muttering )

693
00:39:14,051 --> 00:39:16,497
Oh, for Pete's sake.

694
00:39:16,520 --> 00:39:18,966
Oh, God.

695
00:39:18,989 --> 00:39:21,435
He was so sweet.
( muttering )

696
00:39:21,459 --> 00:39:22,767
Oh, God.

697
00:39:22,793 --> 00:39:25,569
God damn it, Lorna,
stop that whining!

698
00:39:25,596 --> 00:39:27,598
Now if we don't clean this up
in a hurry,

699
00:39:27,631 --> 00:39:29,372
we're gonna get into
all sorts of trouble.

700
00:39:29,400 --> 00:39:31,311
He called me
his little yellow rose.

701
00:39:31,335 --> 00:39:33,611
And I was his sweet
desert rose.

702
00:39:33,637 --> 00:39:35,639
( Lorna muttering )

703
00:39:35,673 --> 00:39:38,517
And I loved him the most.
I really did. Oh, God.

704
00:39:38,542 --> 00:39:40,180
Just give me that knife.

705
00:39:40,211 --> 00:39:42,555
Lorna: He was so nice to me
when he wasn't being a shit.

706
00:39:42,580 --> 00:39:44,617
Oh, my God.

707
00:39:44,648 --> 00:39:46,650
Hell of a good time
we're having, huh?

708
00:39:46,684 --> 00:39:49,187
Lorna: Dale, can you ever
forgive me? Please forgive me.

709
00:39:49,220 --> 00:39:51,564
-( Knife buzzing )
- Oh, God.

710
00:39:58,396 --> 00:40:01,400
Well, butter my ass
and call me a biscuit.

711
00:40:01,432 --> 00:40:05,005
Where did you learn how to work
an electronical device like that?

712
00:40:05,035 --> 00:40:07,481
Shop class.

713
00:40:07,505 --> 00:40:10,145
- Shop class?
- Yeah.

714
00:40:10,174 --> 00:40:12,211
Remember last July

715
00:40:12,243 --> 00:40:14,655
when I was laid off
from work?

716
00:40:14,678 --> 00:40:18,057
I had nothing to do
but sit in front of a busted fan

717
00:40:18,082 --> 00:40:20,289
and drink Wild Turkey all day.

718
00:40:20,317 --> 00:40:21,819
( Stops buzzing )

719
00:40:21,852 --> 00:40:24,093
I went and took shop class.

720
00:40:24,121 --> 00:40:25,532
( Buzzing )

721
00:40:25,556 --> 00:40:28,730
What on earth did you go
and take a shop class for?

722
00:40:32,563 --> 00:40:35,669
I guess I always kind of liked
cutting stuff up.

723
00:40:35,699 --> 00:40:38,009
Apparently so.

724
00:40:41,772 --> 00:40:44,275
(saw buzzing )

725
00:40:44,308 --> 00:40:46,117
( bones cracking,
loud squelching )

726
00:41:00,958 --> 00:41:02,960
(fly buzzing )

727
00:41:18,409 --> 00:41:20,946
(groans)

728
00:41:33,224 --> 00:41:35,465
(sighs)

729
00:41:39,096 --> 00:41:40,803
Now what?

730
00:41:40,831 --> 00:41:44,108
The Crown blender,
model 15D,

731
00:41:44,134 --> 00:41:46,842
will easily grind ice
without burnout

732
00:41:46,871 --> 00:41:48,782
using a revolutionary

733
00:41:48,806 --> 00:41:52,185
regular interval
pulsation technique.

734
00:41:53,177 --> 00:41:54,451
That's right.

735
00:41:58,816 --> 00:42:00,818
Would you look at that?

736
00:42:02,520 --> 00:42:04,022
Huh.

737
00:42:05,289 --> 00:42:08,202
Is it supposed to be
moving around like that?

738
00:42:09,226 --> 00:42:11,467
- Oh.
- Oh, Lord.

739
00:42:11,495 --> 00:42:13,031
Oh, Lord.

740
00:42:13,063 --> 00:42:14,542
- Oh.
- Stop it.

741
00:42:14,565 --> 00:42:15,566
Oh, jeez.

742
00:42:15,599 --> 00:42:18,773
(shrieking ) Oh, Jesus Christ,
look at my ceiling.

743
00:42:18,802 --> 00:42:20,782
Oh, Jesus Christ.

744
00:42:32,750 --> 00:42:38,325
♪ Tell me you love me ♪

745
00:42:38,355 --> 00:42:44,237
♪ Until the end of time ♪

746
00:42:44,261 --> 00:42:48,732
♪ Tell me your love is mine ♪

747
00:42:48,766 --> 00:42:51,144
♪ Tell me lies ♪

748
00:42:51,168 --> 00:42:55,708
♪ Tell me lies ♪

749
00:42:55,739 --> 00:43:01,519
♪ Tell me you want me ♪

750
00:43:01,545 --> 00:43:04,958
♪ Forever and a day... ♪

751
00:43:04,982 --> 00:43:07,519
(coughing )

