And then
there are the boots.

955
00:57:08,425 --> 00:57:10,701
- Boots?
- Oh, yeah, that's right.

956
00:57:10,727 --> 00:57:13,731
See, I'm a fine
boot connoisseur myself.

957
00:57:13,763 --> 00:57:18,735
I can appreciate a fine specimen
of custom-made footwear when I see it.

958
00:57:18,768 --> 00:57:22,477
And the first time I laid eyes
on Dale's boots

959
00:57:22,505 --> 00:57:25,111
I knew I'd never seen
a pair like that before.

960
00:57:25,141 --> 00:57:27,212
What do Dale's boots
gotta do with the robbery?

961
00:57:27,243 --> 00:57:31,316
Ah, well, allow me
to elucidate.

962
00:57:33,416 --> 00:57:36,090
Now I visited

963
00:57:36,119 --> 00:57:39,692
the Waldorf Savings & Loan
after I read about the deed.

964
00:57:39,722 --> 00:57:42,498
Yeah, and I made nice
with the teller.

965
00:57:42,525 --> 00:57:43,731
He's an old-timer.

966
00:57:43,760 --> 00:57:46,832
He's as proud as a parade
to be a part of the great robbery.

967
00:57:46,863 --> 00:57:51,278
And he says to me
that he was just standing at his window

968
00:57:51,301 --> 00:57:53,804
when this highwayman
just waltzed right up to him

969
00:57:53,837 --> 00:57:55,839
and demanded the money.

970
00:57:55,872 --> 00:58:00,218
He says the man acted
like he owned the world

971
00:58:00,243 --> 00:58:03,247
and, hell, wearing a pair of boots
like he was wearing,

972
00:58:03,279 --> 00:58:05,418
